node.text:
Did a little seasonal twist on my favorite kale salad! Made with apples, almonds, parmesan, garlic, and lemon. I made this dish at the beautiful @flamingo_estate!!

A little side note: They called me Chef Carina, which is super sweet, but I don't typically call myself a chef, since I don't have chef experience or training! Always need to throw that out there, because I'm a home cook and a food blogger and really admire chefs who've put in proper time in the kitchen. 

#kale #kalesalad

node.title: Fall/Winter Kale Salad with Flamingo Estate

node.text:
Summer Squash Hash with Jalapeño Scallion Aioli!

Yellow squash sautéed with red onion topped with a fried egg, garlic aioli mixed with scallion, jalapeño, and sesame oil; finished off with some aleppo pepper and dill

If you want the full recipe with ingredient list, it’s available to paid subscribers of “good mood food.” Link in bio & below

https://www.goodmoodfood.news/p/summer-squash-hash

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Carina Wolff on August 18, 2021 tagging @myhealthydish. May be an image of food.

node.text:
Firecracker Salmon Bowl with Fried Avocado, Jalapeño, and Scallion over rice and greens! 

I saw @myhealthydish make a firecracker salmon wrapped in rice paper, but I just made some slight modifications to turn it into a bowl! It was incredible and so nourishing

I seared the salmon in some avocado oil and then fried some sliced jalapeño, avocado slices, and roughly chopped scallion in the same pan right after. Made her sauce using sesame oil, soy sauce, rice vinegar, brown sugar, cilantro, and sesame seeds!

For full details and recipe amounts, head to @myhealthydish’s page — recipe was from last week on her reels!!

node.text:
Blistered Shishito Peppers with Lemon Cilantro Garlic Feta!! 

I love shishitos so much! Who else?

RECIPE

4 oz feta
2 large cloves garlic, finely chopped
Juice of 1 lemon
2 tbsp chopped cilantro
1 1/2 tbsp avocado oil
6 oz shishito peppers

In a small bowl, mix together feta, garlic, lemon, and cilantro. Set aside while you prepare the peppers.

In a large pan or cast iron skillet, heat up the avocado oil on medium high heat. Add the peppers, and cook for a few minutes until they begin to puff up and turn brown.

Transfer to a plate and top with feta mixture and more cilantro!

node.text:
CAPRESE-INSPIRED GREEK YOGURT DIP 🍅 

Posting this as a photo too because my reel doesn’t seem to show up on people’s feeds!!

Eat it with toasted sourdough, crackers, or even mix it with fried eggs (yes, I did that!)

RECIPE (serves 4)
1 pint cherry tomatoes
1/4 cup olive oil
1 cup Greek yogurt
1 clove garlic, minced
4-5 large basil leaves, thinly sliced
Drizzle of balsamic vinegar

Preheat oven to 425 F. Spread tomatoes in a baking dish, and toss with olive oil and a pinch of salt. Bake for 25 minutes.

In a small bowl, mix together Greek yogurt, crushed garlic, and a dash of salt. When tomatoes are ready, spoon them over the yogurt. Top with basil and some balsamic vinegar

node.text:
Elote-Inspired Summer Salad with Lime Grilled Chicken and Avocado!!!! 

I used the “Everything But The Elote” Seasoning from Trader Joe’s for this one, and loaded the salad up with red and green onion, cilantro, roasted corn, cotija cheese, and a Greek-yogurt based dressing with lime and seasoning.

When people refer to elote, which actually means corn cob in Spanish, they’re often referencing a type of Mexican street corn that is typically served with butter, mayo, cotija cheese, and seasoning. When making this recipe, I couldn’t decide whether to call this salad “Elote-inspired” or “Esquites-inspired,” since esquites is the version that’s off the cob, but since I used the Trader Joe’s elote seasoning, I decided to keep it consistent. This is of course not a traditional elote prep, but the flavors are inspired by its flavors!

Full recipe went out on my newsletter today, but you can peep the recipe through the link in my bio!! (Click the corresponding pic, or head to the url below)

https://www.goodmoodfood.news/p/elote-inspired-summer-salad

node.text:
Roasted Red Pepper Quinoa!!! 

I loooove this recipe. It’s kinda like a risotto, but with quinoa, and you roast some red peppers, purée some, chop up the rest, and then add in some garlic, onions, Parmesan and fresh basil for allll the flavor.

Recipe went on today on my newsletter, “good mood food!” It’s also linked in my bio (click the corresponding pic), but be sure to subscribe to future issues so you can get allll of the recipes directly to your inbox! ❤️

https://www.goodmoodfood.news/p/roasted-red-pepper-quinoa

node.text:
Mini Plant-Based Guac Quesadillas!! 🥑 

Anyone remember these from last year? I used street taco sized tortillas and filled them with them plant based cheddar and a makeshift guac made with avocado, red onion, cilantro, and lime!

Fry in a pan for a couple minutes on both sides. You can use olive oil but butter works really well too if you eat dairy. Covering the pan helps the cheese melt too! Obviously same thing can be done with regular sized tortillas and regular cheese 🥰

node.text:
Tomato, Peach and Halloumi Salad topped with fresh mint! Summer in a bowl, sweet and savory, tangy and light, crisp and delish!!

RECIPE
3 large heirloom tomatoes
2 peaches
1 tbsp red wine vinegar
1 tbsp olive oil
8 oz halloumi, cut into 1-inch squares
Small handful of fresh mint leaves

Core tomatoes and cut into wedges. Add to a large bowl with a pinch of salt and toss. Set aside to marinate.

Cut peaches into slices, and set aside while you make the halloumi.

Heat a pan on medium-high heat and add olive oil. Add the halloumi slices, and cook for 2-3 minutes on each side until just golden.

Transfer the peaches and the halloumi to the bowl with the tomatoes, and toss with red wine vinegar. Serve topped with fresh mint and a little cracked pepper
